==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Limpkin
<hw>Limp"kin</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧mp"k⟦icr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Either one of two species of wading birds of the
genus <gen>Aramus</gen>, intermediate between the cranes and rails. The
limpkins are remarkable for the great length of the toes. One species
(<spn>Aramus giganteus</spn>) inhabits Florida and the West Indies; the
other (<spn>Aramus scolopaceus</spn>) is found in South America. Called
also <altname>courlan</altname>, and <altname>crying
bird</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Limpness</ent>⟦br⟧
